1	//! `rw-vn100` — read and configure a VectorNav VN-100 IMU over serial.
2	//!
3	//! The VN-100 speaks an ASCII protocol over a serial port. Each command is
4	//!
5	//! ```text
6	//! $<payload>*XX\r\n
7	//! ```
8	//!
9	//! where `XX` is the 8-bit XOR checksum of every character of `<payload>`
10	//! (i.e. everything between `$` and `*`). Replies echo the same form; binary
11	//! outputs (register 75) use a packed frame ending in a 16-bit CRC instead.
12	//!
13	//! Commands implemented here:
14	//!   get-ascii / set-ascii read/write the ASCII async preset    (register 6)
15	//!   set-ascii-hz          write the ASCII async rate           (register 7)
16	//!   get-bin / set-bin     read / enable-disable binary output   (register 75)
17	//!   set-bin-fields        write the Common field mask           (register 75)
18	//!   set-bin-hz            write the binary rate (reg-75 divisor, 800/hz)
19	//!   baud                  change the serial baud rate          (register 5)
20	//!   rrg / wrg             generic read/write of any register   ($VNRRG / $VNWRG)
21	//!   bench                 passively measure the live stream — ASCII line rate,
22	//!                         binary frame rate, and wire throughput (no writes)
23	//!   reset / factory-reset reboot / restore defaults            ($VNRST / $VNRFS)
24	//!
25	//! Key VN messages:
26	//!   $VNRRG,<id>*XX          -> $VNRRG,<id>,<f1>,...*YY   (read register)
27	//!   $VNWRG,<id>,<f1>,...*XX  -> echo                     (write register)
28	//!   $VNWNV*XX               -> $VNWNV*YY                 (save all to flash)
29	//!   $VNERR,<code>*XX                                     (error; see error_description)
30	//!
31	//! The async output rate (register 7) is one of a fixed firmware set
32	//! (`VALID_RATES`); a value that's out of range — or too much data for the
33	//! current baud — returns a `$VNERR` (0x0C = insufficient baud rate).
34	//!
35	//! Register/enum/table values are cited to the ICD and vnsdk in REFERENCE.md.
36	
37	use std::time::Duration;
38	
39	mod bench;
40	mod cli;
41	mod proto;
42	mod transact;
43	use bench::*;
44	use cli::*;
